## Plan

**SCOPE DECISION (recommend A-now, defer Hugo):** The bead says "likely using Hugo."
Recommend NOT adopting Hugo for v1. The hand-written narrative docs (docs/{init,
capture,run,sync,replay,bench,gc,reindex}.md + docs/README.md + top-level README)
already satisfy "public docs for implemented behavior." The tight, dependency-free,
high-value deliverable is auto-generating a CLI flag/synopsis REFERENCE from the
cobra tree and committing it under docs/cli/, guarded against drift. Hugo is a
separable, heavier static-site commitment; the markdown produced here is already
the content source if a site is wanted later. Doing Hugo now is the main risk
(new toolchain, theme, CI/deploy) for little gain over clean committed markdown.
DEFER Hugo to its own bead with that reasoning recorded.

**Approach:** Add a small standalone generator at cmd/gen-docs/main.go that builds
the real root command via the already-exported cli.NewRootCommand(io.Discard,
io.Discard) and calls cobra/doc.GenMarkdownTreeCustom into docs/cli/. cobra v1.10.2
already ships github.com/spf13/cobra/doc (GenMarkdownTree/GenMarkdownTreeCustom) -
NO new dependency. A standalone cmd (not a hidden subcommand) keeps the production
binary clean and is trivially invokable from make/go:generate/CI.

**DETERMINISM (critical):** cobra/doc appends "###### Auto generated by spf13/cobra
on <date>" unless cmd.DisableAutoGenTag is true (verified md_docs.go:112-113). The
generator MUST walk the whole command tree and set DisableAutoGenTag=true on the
root AND every subcommand before generating, so committed files are timestamp-free
and diff-stable. Use GenMarkdownTreeCustom with a no-op/relative linkHandler and a
filePrepender that emits only a stable "do-not-edit; run make docs" banner (no date).

